---
/**
 * IntellectualBattlefield: A high-impact banner about the power of ideas.
 * Based on Machen's "Moving Armies" quote.
 */
---

<section class="relative py-32 overflow-hidden bg-primary text-white">
  <!-- Decorative background element / "Battlefield" feel -->
  <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-10 pointer-events-none overflow-hidden">
    <div
      class="absolute -right-20 -top-20 w-96 h-96 border-[20px] border-white/20 rounded-full"
    >
    </div>
    <div
      class="absolute left-1/4 bottom-0 w-1 h-64 bg-gradient-to-t from-white/40 to-transparent"
    >
    </div>
    <div
      class="absolute right-1/4 top-0 w-1 h-64 bg-gradient-to-b from-white/40 to-transparent"
    >
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 relative z-10 text-center">
    <div class="flex justify-center mb-10">
      <div class="w-12 h-1 bg-secondary"></div>
    </div>

    <h2
      class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.4em] text-secondary mb-8"
    >
      La Urgencia del Intelecto
    </h2>

    <blockquote
      class="text-3xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-display font-black leading-tight tracking-tight mb-12"
    >
      "Lo que hoy es un asunto de <span
        class="italic font-serif text-secondary/90">especulación académica</span
      >, mañana comienza a mover ejércitos y derribar imperios."
    </blockquote>

    <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-6">
      <p class="text-lg opacity-70 font-serif max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
        Las ideas no son neutrales. Tienen consecuencias que moldean la
        historia. El cristiano no puede ignorar el campo de batalla del
        pensamiento sin entregar el futuro.
      </p>

      <footer class="mt-4">
        <span class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-secondary"
          >— Princeton, 1912</span
        >
      </footer>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
